<paragraph blockId="84.[163,1071,270,643]" pageId="84" pageNumber="467">
R e c o g n i t i o n The male of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="DOLLFUSS" authorityYear="2013" box="[525,724,270,292]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Ammophila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="84" pageNumber="467" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="persica">
<emphasis box="[525,724,270,292]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="467">Ammophila persica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is small (length 
<quantity box="[901,978,270,292]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="84" pageNumber="467" unit="mm" value="14.0">14 mm</quantity>
), slender with a forewing with three submarginal cells, black legs, the pronotal collar coarsely transversely rugose, the gastral apex black without a metallic shine and the supraantennal lamellate projection is absent. In addition, the mesothoracic venter is not distinctly prominent anteriorly, the episternal sulcus ends at the level of the scrobe, the arolia are well developed and the claws without basal tooth. The male of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="DOLLFUSS" authorityYear="2013" box="[906,1070,417,438]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Ammophila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="84" pageNumber="467" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="schmideggeri">
<emphasis box="[906,1070,417,438]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="467">A. schmideggeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="DOLLFUSS" authorityYear="2013" box="[296,402,446,467]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Ammophila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="84" pageNumber="467" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="persica">
<emphasis box="[296,402,446,467]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="467">A. persica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having red legs and a differently shaped clypeus (
<figureCitation box="[967,1059,446,468]" captionStart="Figs 227-239" captionStartId="149.[163,203,1399,1419]" captionTargetBox="[168,1066,225,1359]" captionTargetId="figure-1@149.[163,1070,204,1378]" captionTargetPageId="149" captionText="Figs 227-239: male clypeus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341179" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341179/files/figure.png" pageId="84" pageNumber="467">Fig. 235</figureCitation>
). The male of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": KOHL" authorityYear="1884" box="[297,393,475,497]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Ammophila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="84" pageNumber="467" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="striata">
<emphasis box="[297,393,475,497]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="467">A. striata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="DOLLFUSS" authorityYear="2013" box="[531,635,475,497]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Ammophila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="84" pageNumber="467" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="persica">
<emphasis box="[531,635,475,497]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="467">A. persica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having the gastral apex with a metallic shine. The male of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="DOLLFUSS" authorityYear="2013" box="[364,468,505,526]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Ammophila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="84" pageNumber="467" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="persica">
<emphasis box="[364,468,505,526]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="467">A. persica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="SICKMANN" authorityYear="1894" box="[606,715,505,526]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Ammophila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="84" pageNumber="467" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sinensis">
<emphasis box="[606,715,505,526]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="467">A. sinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having the mesothoracic venter anteriorly not prominent, the episternal sulcusis ending at the level of scrobe and a differently shaped clypeus (
<figureCitation box="[449,539,563,585]" captionStart="Figs 253-261" captionStartId="151.[163,203,1424,1444]" captionTargetBox="[171,1070,230,1402]" captionTargetId="figure-1@151.[163,1070,204,1404]" captionTargetPageId="151" captionText="Figs 253-261: (253-256) male clypeus; (257-261) pronotal collar of male in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341183" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341183/files/figure.png" pageId="84" pageNumber="467">Fig. 256</figureCitation>
). The male of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="F. MORAWITZ" authorityYear="1890" box="[693,828,563,584]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Ammophila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="84" pageNumber="467" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="occipitalis">
<emphasis box="[693,828,563,584]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="467">A. occipitalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="DOLLFUSS" authorityYear="2013" box="[967,1071,563,585]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Ammophila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="84" pageNumber="467" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="persica">
<emphasis box="[967,1071,563,585]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="467">A. persica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having red legs and a mesothoracic venter anteriorly concave, the depression is margined by a carina that forms one small projection on each side.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="84.[163,1071,659,1061]" pageId="84" pageNumber="467">
D e s c r i p t i o n 3: 
<quantity box="[424,501,659,681]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="84" pageNumber="467" unit="mm" value="14.0">14 mm</quantity>
. Black except tergum I, gastral segment II (both with black stripe dorsally) and segment III (partly) red. Clypeus, frons, pronotal lobe, mesopleuron, metapleuron and propodeum laterally and posterolaterally covered with appressed silvery setae; erect setae silvery-white. Clypeus slightly elongate (
<figureCitation box="[967,1058,746,768]" captionStart="Figs 253-261" captionStartId="151.[163,203,1424,1444]" captionTargetBox="[171,1070,230,1402]" captionTargetId="figure-1@151.[163,1070,204,1404]" captionTargetPageId="151" captionText="Figs 253-261: (253-256) male clypeus; (257-261) pronotal collar of male in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341183" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341183/files/figure.png" pageId="84" pageNumber="467">Fig. 256</figureCitation>
), disk flat (
<figureCitation box="[270,365,776,798]" captionStart="Figs 357-373" captionStartId="158.[163,203,1234,1254]" captionTargetBox="[163,1065,241,1187]" captionTargetId="figure-1@158.[163,1070,204,1214]" captionTargetPageId="158" captionText="Figs 357-373: male clypeus in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341197" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341197/files/figure.png" pageId="84" pageNumber="467">Fig. 373</figureCitation>
). Frons densely, vertex sparsely punctate. Pronotal collar slightly irregularly, transversely ridged, shiny (
<figureCitation box="[571,663,805,827]" captionStart="Figs 253-261" captionStartId="151.[163,203,1424,1444]" captionTargetBox="[171,1070,230,1402]" captionTargetId="figure-1@151.[163,1070,204,1404]" captionTargetPageId="151" captionText="Figs 253-261: (253-256) male clypeus; (257-261) pronotal collar of male in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341183" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341183/files/figure.png" pageId="84" pageNumber="467">Fig. 261</figureCitation>
), scutum coarsely transversely rugosereticulate, admedian line distinct. Scutellum coarsely, irregularly longitudinally rugose, metanotum coarsely reticulate. Mesopleuron, metapleuron and propodeum laterally coarsely reticulate. Propodeal enclosure coarsely reticulate and covered with sparse appressed silvery setae medially, more regularly obliquely rugose and glabrous laterally. Mesothoracic venter anteriorly not prominent, episternal sulcus ending at level of scrobe, arolia well developed, claws without basal tooth. Gonostyle laterally: 
<figureCitation box="[910,1002,981,1003]" captionStart="Figs 430-443" captionStartId="163.[163,203,1554,1574]" captionTargetBox="[168,1051,226,1527]" captionTargetId="figure-1@163.[163,1070,204,1534]" captionTargetPageId="163" captionText="Figs 430-443: male genitalia: gonostyle in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341207" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341207/files/figure.png" pageId="84" pageNumber="467">Fig. 443</figureCitation>
; penis valve laterally: 
<figureCitation box="[325,414,1010,1032]" captionStart="Figs 491-508" captionStartId="167.[163,203,1481,1501]" captionTargetBox="[170,1035,220,1461]" captionTargetId="figure-1@167.[163,1070,204,1461]" captionTargetPageId="167" captionText="Figs 491-508: male genitalia: penis valve in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341216" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341216/files/figure.png" pageId="84" pageNumber="467">Fig. 497</figureCitation>
, ventrally: 
<figureCitation box="[533,621,1010,1032]" captionStart="Figs 546-562" captionStartId="170.[163,203,1352,1372]" captionTargetBox="[163,1069,224,1315]" captionTargetId="figure-1@170.[163,1070,204,1332]" captionTargetPageId="170" captionText="Figs 546-562: male genitalia: penis valve in ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341222" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341222/files/figure.png" pageId="84" pageNumber="467">Fig. 562</figureCitation>
, apically: 
<figureCitation box="[730,820,1010,1032]" captionStart="Figs 597-608" captionStartId="172.[163,203,758,778]" captionTargetBox="[182,1032,196,702]" captionTargetId="figure-1@172.[163,1049,196,737]" captionTargetPageId="172" captionText="Figs 597-608: male genitalia: penis valve in apical view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341226" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341226/files/figure.png" pageId="84" pageNumber="467">Fig. 608</figureCitation>
. Flagellomere I: II=1.8- 2.0; length of petiole = hindtarsomeres I+II to I+II+0.75×III.
</paragraph>
